    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix race condition in log memory buffer handling\n\n### Summary\nThere is a race condition in the log memory buffer handling code that can cause incorrect resource block allocation violating scheduling constraints. The issue occurs in `log_output_memory()` where the buffer index is updated before data is copied, and the active side is switched before data is safely written.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/LOG/log.c`: Fixed order of operations in log memory buffer handling to ensure data is copied before buffer index update and side switching\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder high logging load with multiple threads, the race condition can cause:\n1. Data corruption in log buffers\n2. Incorrect buffer index values leading to memory access violations\n3. Segfaults in the log flushing thread\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Enable high-frequency logging in a multi-threaded environment\n2. Run the system under load for an extended period\n3. Monitor for segfaults in the log handling code or corrupted log output\n\nThe issue is most likely to manifest when the log buffers are frequently switching between sides due to high volume logging.\n\n"
}